subSubSection.paragraph:
Like 

Vampyrodes caraccioli

, 

V. major

has a litter size of one (
Davis et al., 1964
; 
Jones, 1964
; 
Jones et al., 1971
). Reproductive data suggested seasonal polyestry; pregnant females have been captured in all months but in December (
Davis et al., 1964
; 
Jones, 1964
; 
Jones et al., 1971
; 
Valdez and LaVal, 1971
; 
Fleming et al., 1972
; 
Thomas, 1972
; 
Bonaccorso, 1979
; 
Estrada and Coates-Estrada, 2001
). Lactating females have been captured from January to September (
Davis et al., 1964
; 
Thomas, 1972
; 
Bonaccorso, 1979
).

The X chromosome is subtelocentric and the Y chromosome is submetacentric (
Baker, 1973
).
